el":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":8184,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/15\/feeding-household-charity\/","url_meta":{"origin":3598,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sadaqa: Feeding your household is charity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 15, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Miqdam ibn Ma\u2019di reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhat you feed yourself is your charity, what you feed your children is your charity, what you feed your wife is your charity, and what you feed your servant is your charity.\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6667,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/19\/slaves-equal-treament\/","url_meta":{"origin":3598,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Equality: Slaves are equals in food, clothing, dignity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Ma\u2019rur ibn Suwayd reported: I met Abu Dharr while he was wearing the same clothes as his servant boy. I asked him about it, and he said, \"I once abused a man and insulted his mother, so the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said to me, 'O Abu\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7686,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/05\/prophet-never-says-no-charity\/","url_meta":{"origin":3598,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Charity: The Prophet never refused to give in charity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was never asked anything for which he said no. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5687, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2311 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u00a0\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0633\u064f\u0626\u0650\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064f\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0634\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0621\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0637\u064f\u0651 \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6183,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/10\/greet-peace-do-not-know\/","url_meta":{"origin":3598,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Islam: Greet strangers with peace","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 10, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr\u00a0reported: A man asked the Prophet, \u201cWhich Islam is best?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be up